invoke and status commands in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\\n\\n## Base Specifications\\n\\n- **AR**: AR-023\\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\\n- **Language**: Python\\n- **Size**: M\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Background\\n\\nThe `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to deployed agents via the AgentCube Router or standard Kubernetes Service. The `status` command retrieves and displays the current status of deployed agents. Both commands work with either the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) or the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + Service).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Requirements\\n\\n### AR-023-001: invoke CLI interface\\n\\nThe system SHALL expose the `invoke` command via Typer with specific options.\\n\\n#### Scenario: AR-023-001-A — Invoke command options\\n\\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help`\\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\\n  - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \\\".\\\")\\n  - `--payload JSON` — JSON-formatted input passed to the agent (default: \\\"{}\\\")\\n  - `--header KEY:VALUE` — Custom HTTP headers (repeatable)\\n  - `--provider PROVIDER` — Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' (default: \\\"agentcube\\\")\\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\\n\\n#### Scenario: AR-023-001-B — Default options\\n\\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke` with no options\\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be applied:\\n  - `workspace`: `\\\".\\\"`\\n  - `payload`: `\\\"{}\\\"`\\n  - `header_list`: `None`\\n  - `provider`: `\\\"agentcube\\\"`\\n  - `verbose`: `False`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### AR-023-002: invoke payload parsing...\n  Line 23: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775863824949,\"sessionID\":\"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79bb7c2e001svmV8kun2Pw0mF\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79bb6b13001PJLV20mES7uW0z\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_28645eb9cffeDEBJBa63mnSzqs\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Done. Created `/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md` with 14 requirements and 30+ GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios covering:\\n\\n- *