: - **THEN** the system SHALL send an HTTP POST request to the endpoint and display the response\\n25: \\n26: #### Scenario: Invoke without published endpoint\\n27: - **GIVEN** the workspace has not been published or `agent_endpoint` is missing\\n28: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke`\\n29: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the agent has not been published\\n30: \\n31: ### Requirement: `status` command\\n32: \\n33: The system SHALL provide a `status` subcom...\n  Line 13: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775857436749,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d795a040d001K1tgFNLY4B96E3\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7959f36c001cCgp4Wk1lNbIbJ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_2264f0d6091e47fdaf132fa6\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\\n2: \\n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\\n4: **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\\n5: \\n6: ---\\n7: \\n8: ## T-1: InvokeRuntime class skeleton + constructor\\n9: \\n10: - [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\\n11: - [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \\\"agentcube\\\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\\n12: - [ ] Add `InvokeRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\\n13: - [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly (default and explicit values)\\n14: \\n15: ## T-2: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites\\n16: \\n17: - [ ] Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path: Path) -> tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]`\\n18: - [ ] Load metadata via `MetadataService`; raise `ValueError` if `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint` is missing\\n19: - [ ] Return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\\n20: - [ ] Write test: valid workspace with published metadata returns tuple\\n21: - [ ] Write test: missing `agent_id` raises `ValueError`\\n22: - [ ] Write test: missing `agent_endpoint` raises `ValueError`\\n23: \\n24: ## T-3: InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation\\n25: \\n26: - [ ] Implement `_direct_http_invocation(endpoint: str, payload: Dict, headers: Dict[str, str], workspace_pa...\n  Line 22: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775857446861,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d795a2b92001hbbHkngVwGHTzn\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d795a1f50001SUwCcDhTOH7Q3K\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_e8a5f38ba1c74134b3e97ef2\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/design.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design\\n2: \\n3: ## Overview\\n4: \\n5: The `invoke` command sends HTTP POST requests to a deployed agent endpoint and displays the response. The `status` command queries the deployment status of an agent from Kubernetes or workspace metadata and renders it as a Rich Table. Together they complete the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke/status`.\\n6: \\n7: Both commands are **not yet implemented** — this design specifies the full technical implementation.\\n8: \\n9: ---\\n10: \\n11: ## Architecture\\n12: \\n13: ### 2.1 Data Flow\\n14: \\n15: ```\\n16: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n17: │                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\\n18: │   kubectl-agentcube invoke -f <ws> --payload '{}' [--header ...]     │\\n19: │   kubectl-agentcube status -f <ws> [--provider agentcube|k8s]        │\\n20: └────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\n21:                          │\\n22:           ┌──────────────┴──────────────┐\\n23:           ▼                             ▼\\n24: ┌─────────────────────┐       ┌─────────────────────┐\\n25: │    InvokeRuntime    │       │    StatusRuntime    │\\n26: │                     │       │                     │\\n27: │ .invoke()           │       │ .get_status()       │\\n28: │  ├─ _valid...\n  Line 36: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775857479565,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d795a812400161vJjpJ5BX3bTu\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d795a771a001G4BfwZrohzo8i5\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Based on my analysis of the codebase, here's the summary:\\n\\n## AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Archive Summary\\n\\n### Completed\\n\\n**InvokeRuntime** (`invoke_runtime.py`):\\n- Constructor with `verbose` and `provider` params\\n- `_validate_invoke_prerequisites()` — loads metadata, validates `agent_id` and `agent_endpoint`\\n- `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube()` — async HTTP POST with URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR, session header injection\\n- `_direct_http_invocation()` — async HTTP POST for standard K8s endpoints\\n- `invoke()` — orchestration routing by provider\\n\\n**StatusRuntime** (`status_runtime.py`):\\n- Constructor with `verbose` and `provider` params\\n- `_get_cr_k8s_status()` — queries AgentRuntime CR via `AgentCubeProvider`\\n- `_get_k8s_status()` — delegates to `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()`\\n- `get_status()` — orchestration routing by provider, returns `not_published` if no `agent_id`\\n\\n**KubernetesProvider** extension:\\n- `get_agent_status()` — queries deployment status, handles 404 gracefully\\n\\n**CLI commands** (`cli/main.py`):\\n- `invoke` command — JSON payload parsing, header parsing (`key:value`), provider selection, Rich output\\n- `status` command — Rich Table rendering, `not_published` guidance, error handling\\n- Both commands use `_handle_error()` for consistent error reporting\\n\\n**Tests**:\\n- `test_invoke_runtime.py` — constructor, valid invoke (both providers), not published, missing endpoint, URL rewriting, session header, custom headers, HTTP error, validate prerequisites\\n- `test_status_runtime.py` — constructor, not published, CR exists/no-status/not-found, K8s running/pending/not-found, provider selection/override\\n- `test_invoke_command.py` — success (both providers), default/custom payload, in...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-023_ST-4.log:\n  Line 10: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775856121550,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ba319cffeYTa9meQOZzGA4C\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7945f2840019wAI1gwd7XG7fB\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7945dd14001On9xusb1vwIfhh\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ba319cffeYTa9meQOZzGA4C\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_db007097be8a4bd48349f551\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\\n2: \\n3: ## Context\\n4: \\n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\\n6: - **Language:** Python\\n7: - **Size:** M\\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`\\n9: \\n10: ## Scope\\n11: \\n12: This delta spec covers the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands, their runtime classes (`InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`), and associated provider integrations (`AgentCubeProvider`, `KubernetesProvider`).\\n13: \\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: ## invoke Command\\n17: \\n18: ### Requirement: invoke command entry point\\n19: \\n20: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that POSTs JSON payload to the published agent endpoint, supporting both `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service) providers.\\n21: \\n22: #### Scenario: invoke options and defaults\\n23: \\n24: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\\n25: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be:\\n26:   - `workspace` = `\\\".\\\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\\n27:   - `payload` = `\\\"{}\\\"` (`--payload`, `str`)\\n28:   - `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`)\\n29:   - `provider` = `\\\"agentcube\\\"` (`--provider`, `str`)\\n30:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\\n31: \\n32: #### Scenario: payload JSON parsing\\n33: \\n34: - **GIVEN** the user provides `--payload '{\\\"input\\\": \\\"hello\\\"}'`\\n35: - **WHEN** the command parses it\\n36: - **THEN** the system SHALL deserialize it to...\n  Line 44: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775856216786,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ba319cffeYTa9meQOZzGA4C\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7946ab00001xqgEEkJ9thBNNU\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7946986b001JUuXIuw2iKdqSf\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ba319cffeYTa9meQOZzGA4C\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"call_1d7d064c31de446881a0344b\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\\n\\n**Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\\n**Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## T-1: InvokeRuntime class skeleton + constructor\\n\\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\\n- [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \\\"agentcube\\\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\\n- [ ] Add `InvokeRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\\n- [ ] Write test: constructor sets `ver