nvoke(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\\n40: ```\\n41: \\n42: ### StatusRuntime\\n43: \\n44: ```python\\n45: class StatusR...\n  Line 16: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775855944275,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79419a2b0010mBY34Ew6hfcIf\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79418c27001ALc1R3MddFOTBb\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"task\",\"callID\":\"call_fc5c352ef4124e3c91cda251\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"description\":\"Explore invoke/status source code\",\"prompt\":\"I need to understand the actual implementation of the invoke and status commands in the agentcube CLI project. Please explore the following files and return their full contents:\\n\\n1. Find and read `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` - look for invoke() and status() functions\\n2. Find and read `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` - full InvokeRuntime class\\n3. Find and read `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` - full StatusRuntime class\\n4. Find and read `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` - especially get_agent_runtime method\\n5. Find and read `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` - especially get_agent_status method\\n6. Find and read any test files related to invoke or status commands\\n\\nAlso check if there are any existing tests for these commands.\\n\\nReturn the full file contents for each file found, along with the file paths.\",\"subagent_type\":\"explore\"},\"output\":\"task_id: ses_286be54ceffeYl7uK1tpbR3xQ7 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\\n\\n<task_result>\\nNow I have a complete picture. Here is my comprehensive findings report:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary: Invoke and Status Commands in AgentCube CLI\\n\\n### Key Finding: These commands are NOT YET IMPLEMENTED\\n\\nThe `invoke` and `status` commands, along with their runtime classes (`InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`), are **planned but not implemented**. They exist only in specification/design documents and task lists. All tasks in `changes/AR-023/tasks.md` are unchecked.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Files That EXIST (with full contents already returned above)\\n\\n### 1. `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/...\n  Line 19: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775855948354,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79434e15001B0m5JIlDZjrfZr\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d794342ac001Ldk8hG1Y597lf8\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_835564d1ca844f6fa0ce895d\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\\n2: \\n3: ## Context\\n4: \\n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\\n6: - **Language:** Python\\n7: - **Size:** M\\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`\\n9: \\n10: ## Scope\\n11: \\n12: This delta spec covers the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands, their runtime classes (`InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`), and associated provider integrations (`AgentCubeProvider`, `KubernetesProvider`).\\n13: \\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: ## invoke Command\\n17: \\n18: ### Requirement: invoke command entry point\\n19: \\n20: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that POSTs JSON payload to the published agent endpoint, supporting both `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service) providers.\\n21: \\n22: #### Scenario: invoke options and defaults\\n23: \\n24: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\\n25: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be:\\n26:   - `workspace` = `\\\".\\\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\\n27:   - `payload` = `\\\"{}\\\"` (`--payload`, `str`)\\n28:   - `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`)\\n29:   - `provider` = `\\\"agentcube\\\"` (`--provider`, `str`)\\n30:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\\n31: \\n32: #### Scenario: payload JSON parsing\\n33: \\n34: - **GIVEN** the user provides `--payload '{\\\"input\\\": \\\"hello\\\"}'`\\n35: - **WHEN** the command parses it\\n36: - **THEN** the system SHALL deserialize it to...\n  Line 20: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775855949558,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d794352c9001BwPDj1rmNyBwrQ\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d794342ac001Ldk8hG1Y597lf8\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_bc924614ebc44b34aee096ee\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令\\n2: \\n3: ## Purpose\\n4: \\n5: 为 AgentCube Python CLI（`kubectl-agentcube`）实现 `invoke` 和 `status` 两个子命令，补全 Agent 从打包、构建、发布到调用和状态查询的完整生命周期。\\n6: \\n7: 当前 CLI 已实现 `pack`、`build`、`publish` 命令，但用户部署 Agent 后无法通过 CLI 验证其是否正常工作或查看运行状态。本 AR 补齐最后两个关键操作。\\n8: \\n9: ## Scope\\n10: \\n11: ### In Scope\\n12: \\n13: 1. **`invoke` 命令**\\n14:    - 向已部署的 Agent 发送 HTTP POST 请求\\n15:    - 支持 `--payload` 传递 JSON 输入（默认 `\\\"{}\\\"`）\\n16:    - 支持 `--header` 添加自定义 HTTP Header（可重复指定）\\n17:    - 支持 `--provider` 选择 `agentcube`（AgentRuntime CR）或 `k8s`（标准 Deployment/Service）\\n18:    - AgentCube Provider 自动将 endpoint 重写为 `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\\n19:    - 若元数据包含 `session_id`，自动添加 `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` Header\\n20:    - 打印响应结果，异常通过 `_handle_error` 处理\\n21: \\n22: 2. **`status` 命令**\\n23:    - 加载 workspace 元数据（`agent_metadata.yaml`）\\n24:    - 根据 `--provider` 查询对应资源状态\\n25:    - AgentCube Provider：通过 `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime` 查询 CR 状态\\n26:    - K8s Provider：通过 `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` 查询 Deployment/Service 状态\\n27:    - 使用 Rich Table 渲染状态信息\\n28:    - `not_published` 或 `error` 状态时打印提示并 `typer.Exit(1)`\\n29: \\n30: 3. **错误处理**\\n31:    - `invoke`：JSON payload 解析失败、Header 格式错误直接退出码 1\\n32:    - 运行时异常统一走 `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)`\\n33: \\n34: ### Out of Scope\\n35: \\n36: - 修复 `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcub...\n  Line 32: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775856104708,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79439591001uHK0v55HBMeuRu\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d794388580017G6msD6HLeV7sK\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"call_38f962d1f18b4741a269b99e\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nThe `invoke` command sends HTTP POST requests to a deployed agent endpoint and displays the response. The `status` command queries the deployment status of an agent from Kubernetes or workspace metadata and renders it as a Rich Table. Together they complete the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke/status`.\\n\\nBoth commands are **not yet implemented** — this design specifies the full technical implementation.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Architecture\\n\\n### 2.1 Data Flow\\n\\n```\\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n│                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\\n│   kubectl-agentcube invoke -f <ws> --payload '{}' [--header ...]     │\\n│   kubectl-agentcube status -f <ws> [--provider agentcube|k8s]        │\\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\n                         │\\n          ┌──────────────┴──────────────┐\\n          ▼                             ▼\\n┌─────────────────────┐       ┌─────────────────────┐\\n│    InvokeRuntime    │       │    StatusRuntime    │\\n│                     │       │                     │\\n│ .invoke()           │       │ .get_status()       │\\n│  ├─ _validate_      │       │  ├─ load metadata   │\\n│  │   prerequisites  │       │  ├─ _get_cr_k8s_    │\\n│  ├─ _invoke_agent_  │       │  │   status()        │\\n│  │   via_agentcube  │       │  └─ _get_k8s_       │\\n│  └─ _direct_http_   │       │     status()        │\\n│     invocation()    │       │                     │\\n└────────┬────────────┘       └────────┬────────────┘\\n         │     ...\n  Line 33: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775856104784,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79439361001Pg75rRPytWvFas\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d794388580017G6msD6HLeV7sK\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have all the context needed. Let me write the comprehensive design.md for AR-023.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775856104782,\"end\":1775856104782}}}\n  Line 36: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775856109033,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7945c283001O2AQZMEezg2dVb\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7945b57f001Hhr0KP6Z0lR5BJ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Design written to `changes/AR-023/design.md`. The LSP errors shown are pre-existing type checking issues in the kubernetes provider files (missing type stubs), not caused by this change.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775856109031,\"end\":1775856109031}}}\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-023_ST-2.log:\n  Line 4: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775855682219,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286c0c990ffeBZf2OlQ192KZ54\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d793f3dbe001SVmBBVwH3gvJ6s\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d793f3765001R0PYdrnZrUOFje\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286c0c990ffeBZf2OlQ192KZ54\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_b94